<DOC><DOCNO> AP900122-0135 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-22-90 1612EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-BerlinWall     01-22 0176</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Berlin Wall,0180</SECOND><HEAD>East Germans Begin Dismantling Berlin Wall</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-East Germany, Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>WEST BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   East German border guards began tearing downa 330-yard section of the Berlin Wall on Monday night to beginreplacing the barrier with a metal fence, a West German officialannounced.   The dismantling work began along the Kreuzberg district thatborders the wall in the southeastern sector of the divided city,said Werner Kolhoff, spokesman for the West Berlin city government.   Kolhoff said an East German border official told him othersections of the wall would be torn down shortly as well, but he wasnot specific about when that would occur.   East Germany's interim president, Manfred Gerlach of the LiberalDemocratic Party, disclosed on Jan. 2 that the wall built in 1961would be replaced with ``normal border markings.''   There had been no public announcement by the East Germangovernment on the dismantling.   Kolhoff said he was informed that the stretch of wall being torndown now would be replaced by a six-foot metal fence by Friday.</TEXT></DOC>